**Never `--no-verify`, never `--no-gpg-sign`, never `--amend`.** **Never `git add -A` or `git add .`** — only explicit paths. These rules apply at every commit-emitting layer: CLI mutation verbs, hook post-commits, agent-driven `git commit` calls. Bypassing hooks or signing, amending shipped commits, or scooping untracked files into a commit by accident are the four ways a clean commit history corrodes — and none of them have legitimate use in this repo. If a hook fails, fix it; if a signature fails, fix it; if a commit shipped wrong, ship a new one.
